Devel-GDB version 2.0
=====================

The Devel::GDB package provides an interface for communicating with GDB,
the GNU debugger.  Complete documentation is available on the CPAN site:

http://search.cpan.org/~JEZRA/Devel-GDB/GDB.pm

INSTALLATION
------------

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES
------------

This module requires these other modules and libraries, which should be
part of most standard Perl instalations:

  Test::More
  threads::shared
  Thread::Semaphore

The following modules are also recommended:

  threads (i.e. Perl compiled with -Dusethreads)
  Expect
  IO::BufferedSelect

In addition, for the module to be useful, you should have gdb installed :-)

